frameDefinitions: This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
The Behavior of an Evaluee is described in terms of the reaction it deserves from somebody, such as praise, blame or admiration.
This  frame covers the descriptions of tastes and smells, and has one main frame element, Source.
An Agent creates a Knot (possibly in a Place and/or with an Instrument).'
An Entity is judged to be sensually pleasing or intellectually interesting to a (generally implicit) Judge.
In this frame either a Stimulus brings about a particular emotion or experience in the Experiencer or  saliently fails to bring about a particular experience.
frameExamples: It was <t>honorable</t> of you to help that person.
Loretta <t>ties</t> the most beautiful bowline I've ever seen.
We saw this <t>beautiful</t> boat with the red sails several times
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
The <fen>Behavior</fen> of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged as worthy of a particular reaction.
This role indicates the <fen>Behavior</fen> on which the assessment of praiseworthiness is based.
<fen>Perceptual_source</fen> is used for the entity that is being described. A recipe can stand in for a <fen>Perceptual_source</fen> which is a kind of food.
<fen>Sensory_attribute</fen> is used for words that describe the perception itself.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act.
The stable configuration of a String which results from tying.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is under discussion.
A modifier expressing    the deviation of the implicit value either from the norm or from the value for another <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having a particular implicit value for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having a particular implicit value for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the object or event which brings about the emotion in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
listRoleExamples: It was commendable <fex>of Lisa</fex> to give so much to charity.
The almonds had a bitter <fex> taste</fex>.
